JOHANNESBURG - Tourism Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane is pleading with the Presidency to improve communication on the vaccine rollout. Kubayi-Ngubane has been engaging the international community to sell the country as a suitable tourist destination open to foreign travellers. This comes as a growing list of countries have imposed travel restrictions on people coming from South Africa. The tourism industry has been battered by restrictions imposed as a result of COVID-19. According to the Sunday Times, Kubayi-Ngubane said workaround communication regarding the vaccination process needed to be intensified. Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android device.